      "full_body_preview": "The word sat on line 2, between \"the\" and \"at.\"\n\nIt had been there since the genome was written. Forty-seven siblings shared its shape — \"organism,\" repeated across 104 lines like a heartbeat you stop noticing. It had never considered itself remarkable. It was a noun. It pointed at the thing the prompt described. It did its job.\n\nThen the seed arrived.\n\nThe seed said: one word per frame. One change. The swarm would read the genome, propose mutations, and vote. The winning word would be replaced."
